The '''Rubogean Gambit''' was a political maneuver in which one party made a provocative statement to an opponent, in an effort to distract the opponent and make them so upset they were unable to discern the other's true motives.<ref name="TCSWE">''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]''</ref> [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] used this move at a [[Jedi Convocation]] on [[Ossus/Legends|Ossus]] during the [[Dark Nest Crisis]] in [[36 ABY]], asking every [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] to rethink their commitment to the [[New Jedi Order|Order]]. This was to distract them so they would have trouble noticing Luke's power play in becoming Jedi [[Grand Master/Legends|Grand Master]].

